If the program runs successfully, you will receive output that is similar to that shown in the following example: Starting Network Server Testing if Network Server is up and running! Network Server now running Got an embedded connection. Testing embedded connection by executing a sample query number of rows in sys.systables = 16 While my app is busy with embedded work, ij might connect like this:
$ java -Dij.user=me -Dij.password=pw -Dij.protocol= jdbc:derby:\\localhost:1527\ org.apache.derby.tools.ij ij> connect 'NSSimpleDB';
Clients can continue to connect: Press [Enter] to stop Server
